==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Filleting
<hw>Fil"let*ing</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Arch.)</fld>
<def>The protecting of a joint, as between roof and parapet wall, with
mortar, or cement, where <xex>flashing</xex> is employed in better
work.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The material of which fillets are made; also,
fillets, collectively.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Fillibeg</ent>⟦br⟧
